in a critical perspective on how plantation life is changing as Darjeeling struggles to reinvent its signature commodity for twenty-first-century consumers. The Darjeeling Distinction challenges fair-trade policy and practice, exposing how trade initiatives often fail to consider the larger environmental, historical, and sociopolitical forces that shape the lives of the people they intended to support.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCompetition, UnfairxIndiaxDarjeeling (District)xIndiaxDarjeeling (District). 0aCompetition, UnfairzIndiazDarjeeling (District) 0aCompetition, UnfairzIndiazDarjeeling (District). 0aTea plantationsxIndiaxDarjeeling (District). 0aTea plantationszIndiaxDarjeeling (District) 0aTea plantationszIndiazDarjeeling (District). 0aTea tradexIndiaxDarjeeling (District). 0aTea tradezIndiazDarjeeling (District) 0aTea tradezIndiazDarjeeling (District). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957602423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520957602.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles